  <!-- ABOUT -->
  <section id="about">
    <h2 class="section-title">About CowCoin</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      CowCoin is a professionally structured meme-inspired project designed for sustainable growth rather than
      short-term speculation. The goal is to combine the simplicity and virality of meme tokens with disciplined
      tokenomics, transparent communication, and gradual utility development.
    </p>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Vision & Objective</h3>
        <p>
          CowCoin aims to build a long-term, community-centric ecosystem around an ERC-20 token with a fixed
          supply and clear governance. The project focuses on:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Transparent on-chain tokenomics and open communication.</li>
          <li>Gradual introduction of utilities such as NFTs, staking, and community rewards.</li>
          <li>Maintaining healthy liquidity and responsible treasury management.</li>
          <li>Providing a simple entry point for users who are new to digital assets.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Core Principles</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Transparency:</strong> Contract is publicly viewable and verifiable on Etherscan.</li>
          <li><strong>No unrealistic promises:</strong> The project avoids guaranteeing returns or price targets.</li>
          <li><strong>Security-minded:</strong> Simple, audited-friendly architecture prioritised over complexity.</li>
          <li><strong>Community focus:</strong> Decisions around utilities and roadmap will involve holders.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="muted">
          CowCoin is a utility and community token, not an investment contract or guarantee of profit.
          Users should always perform independent research.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOKENOMICS -->
  <section id="tokenomics">
    <h2 class="section-title">Tokenomics</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      CowCoin is deployed as a fixed-supply ERC-20 token with straightforward, verifiable parameters. The focus is
      on clarity and sustainability rather than aggressive taxation models.
    </p>
    <div class="tokenomics-grid">
      <div class="tokenomics-item">
        <strong>Total Supply</strong>
        1,000,000,000 COW (one billion tokens) minted at deployment. No additional minting.
      </div>
      <div class="tokenomics-item">
        <strong>Decimals</strong>
        18 decimal places, following the standard for ERC-20 tokens on Ethereum.
      </div>
      <div class="tokenomics-item">
        <strong>Burn & Fees</strong>
        A small portion of transfers may be allocated to burns or ecosystem functions, depending on the final
        contract configuration and governance decisions.
      </div>
      <div class="tokenomics-item">
        <strong>Initial Allocation</strong>
        A portion of supply is reserved for liquidity, a portion for ecosystem incentives, and the remainder for
        treasury and long-term development. Exact allocations will be shared transparently with the community.
      </div>
      <div class="tokenomics-item">
        <strong>Liquidity & Locking</strong>
        Liquidity pool details and any locking or vesting arrangements will be published once live on DEXs or CEXs.
      </div>
      <div class="tokenomics-item">
        <strong>Ownership & Governance</strong>
        Governance and decision-making will gradually move towards community input as the project matures.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ROADMAP -->
  <section id="roadmap">
    <h2 class="section-title">Roadmap</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      The roadmap is designed as a realistic, execution-oriented plan. All milestones are subject to change based on
      market conditions, security reviews, and community feedback.
    </p>
    <div class="roadmap-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="phase-label">Phase 1 ‚Äì Foundation</div>
        <h3>Launch & Validation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Token deployment on Ethereum.</li>
          <li>Initial website and branding.</li>
          <li>Basic community channels (Telegram, X/Twitter, etc.).</li>
          <li>Smart-contract verification on Etherscan.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="phase-label">Phase 2 ‚Äì Liquidity</div>
        <h3>Market Access</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Liquidity provisioning on decentralised exchange(s).</li>
          <li>Listing requests to major tracking platforms (e.g., CoinGecko, CoinMarketCap).</li>
          <li>Transparency reports for circulating supply and liquidity.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="phase-label">Phase 3 ‚Äì Utility</div>
        <h3>Product & Ecosystem</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>NFT collection and community reward mechanisms.</li>
          <li>Light staking or holding incentives, where feasible.</li>
          <li>Partner integrations and ecosystem collaborations.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="phase-label">Phase 4 ‚Äì Expansion</div>
        <h3>Scaling the Community</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Exploration of additional utilities and use-cases.</li>
          <li>Further exchange listings, subject to compliance and demand.</li>
          <li>Continuous improvement based on community and security input.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HOW TO BUY -->
  <section id="how-to-buy">
    <h2 class="section-title">How to Buy CowCoin</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">
      The steps below describe a typical way to acquire ERC-20 tokens on Ethereum. Exact details may change depending
      on the exchanges or wallets you use.
    </p>
    <div class="how-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>1. Set up a wallet</h3>
        <p>
          Install a reputable Ethereum wallet such as MetaMask. Safely back up your seed phrase and never share it
          with anyone. Ensure your wallet is set to the Ethereum Mainnet.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>2. Fund with ETH</h3>
        <p>
          Purchase ETH through a centralised exchange or on-ramp and send it to your wallet address. ETH is required
          both to buy CowCoin and to pay gas fees on Ethereum.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>3. Connect to a DEX</h3>
        <p>
          Connect your wallet to a decentralised exchange that lists CowCoin (such as Uniswap once live). Verify the
          official contract address before trading.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>4. Swap & store safely</h3>
        <p>
          Swap ETH for COW, then verify your transaction on Etherscan. Always double-check the contract address and
          be cautious of phishing links. Consider using hardware wallets for larger holdings.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="muted">
      Digital assets are volatile and involve risk. Only allocate funds you can afford to lose and always perform
      independent research.
    </p>
  </section>

